Academic Symposium on Scientific and Technological Information Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 30 (KCNA) -- An academic symposium on scientific and technological information was sponsored by the Central Committee of the Korean General Federation of Science and Technology at the Grand People's Study House on Nov. 28 and 29.
 It was attended by officials, scientists and technicians in the field of information science and technology including Kim Il Sung University, the Academy of Medical Science, the Central Scientific and Technological Information Agency, Pyongyang Computer College and the Grand People's Study House. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The symposium heard many papers on scientific and technological information which are of significance in developing information technology and the national economy.
 The participants discussed successes and experience achieved in the research method of the third dimension information service including strategy information and tactics information and in the study of the decision support system, database system for information collection and analysis, process and search service and the information search system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also introduced at the symposium were papers on the field of interpretation of morphology and meaning and mechanical translation for dealing with languages and speech recognition technology such as the method of dealing with co-ordinate conjunctions in English-Korean mechanical translation and the search method in continuous speech recognition. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants gave their attention to the modeling of background knowledge for analysis of database of scientific and technological documents, the method of arranging scientific and technological vocabulary in the medical field, the information system for operating and managing the Grand People's Study House, the optimum process  planning by genetic algorithm and others as they are helpful in hastening the introduction of IT in public fields and significant in the study of scientific and technological information. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prizes were awarded to those who presented good papers at the symposium.

Cuban Embassy Officials Visit Military University 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 30 (KCNA) -- Cuban Ambassador to the DPRK Ruben Perez Valdes and embassy officials visited Kim Il Sung Military University and other places on Nov. 28 and 29 on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of the Cuban revolutionary armed forces.
 When they visited the university, they laid bouquets before the statue of President Kim Il Sung there and went round the university. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They inspected the Victorious Fatherland Liberation War Museum.
 After inspection, the ambassador said that the victory of the Korean people who defeated the U.S. imperialists in the Korean war greatly encourages the progressive people of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The friendly relations between the two countries provided by Kim Il Sung and Fidel Castro Ruz will be everlasting, he said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The next leg of their visit was the Fatherland Liberation War Historic Site.
 They attentively looked round several historic buildings, being briefed on the fact that there Kim Il Sung led the whole party, the entire army and all the people to victory in the war with his Juche-oriented military idea, strategy and tactics and extraordinary commanding art. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also inspected the Pyongyang Metro.

Success Made in Creation of Music and Dances 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 30 (KCNA) -- The creators and artistes in the DPRK have made signal success in the creation of music and dance pieces dealing with the revolutionary struggle and diverse aspects of people's life over the last more than decade.
 They created songs successfully representing the undying exploits performed by President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il such as songs "Leader Will Always Be with Us", "We Long to See Your Broad Smile", "Thunder on Jong Il Peak" and "February Is Spring". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "Let Us Hold High the Red Flag", "We Will Defend the Headquarters of Revolution with Our Lives", "In the Spirit of the 'Arduous March'" and other songs instilled confidence of sure victory and optimism into the Korean people dynamically advancing towards a bright morrow despite manifold difficulties and trials. "Blessed My Life", "We Will Never Forget Those Days", "Vast Plain Taehongdan," "Yebbuni," "If Our Mother Party Wishes" and other songs are loved by people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Symphony suite "Long Journey for Songun Leadership", symphony "Pyongyang Is Best", orchestra "Rich Harvest Comes to the Chongsan Plain", "Arirang" and others were created and newly represented. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A lot of dance pieces rich in ideological content and high in artistry have been produced. They include dance "Victory of Revolution Is in Sight", group dance "For the Motherland", female group dance "Janggu Dance".

North-South Media Seminar Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mt. Kumgang Resort, November 29 (KCNA) -- A seminar on the subject of "Implementation of the June 15 Joint Declaration and Role of Mediapersons in the North and the South" was held at Mt. Kumgang Resort on Wednesday.
 The seminar was attended by the members of the north side delegation led by Jo Chung Han, vice-chairman of the media panel committee of the north side's committee for the implementation of the June 15 joint declaration and the members of the south side delegation led by Jong Il Yong, permanent representative of the media headquarters of the south side's committee for the implementation of the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Congratulatory and other speeches were made there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A joint statement on which the north and the south agreed and adopted was made public at the seminar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint statement underlined the need for the mediapersons of the north and the south to take the lead in supporting and implementing the joint declaration and standing against the outside forces' unreasonable interference in the issues of the nation and threat of war and urged them to reject any separatist news service that may hamstring the efforts to implement the declaration and spark confrontation and tension between compatriots and release fair reports to serve the purpose of achieving the national reconciliation and unity and the peace and reunification of the country.
 It called on the above-said panel committee and the headquarters to boost the solidarity and cooperation in the activities to implement the joint declaration.
 The joint statement appealed to all Korean mediapersons at home and abroad to pool their will and wisdom under the banner of "June 15" and "By our nation itself" and conduct positive activities to protect the dignity and interests of the nation and achieve the peace and reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day mediapersons of the north and the south toured the area of Lagoon Samil, sharing compatriotic feelings.

Intensified Struggle against GNP Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 30 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article calls upon all Koreans at home and abroad to intensify the struggle for frustrating the pro-U.S. sycophantic and traitorous acts of the Grand National Party of south Korea and its anti-reunification moves for confrontation and war under the uplifted slogan of "anti-GNP actions."
 The pro-U.S. sycophantic traitors in south Korea including the GNP are working hard to stifle the cause of achieving peace, national independence and reunification in collusion with outside forces, going against the June 15 era of reunification, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP gentry is escalating its reactionary offensive to eliminate the progressive forces from all walks of life desirous of independence and reunification, while busying themselves with tightening the alliance with the U.S. and the system of cooperation with it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This traitorous party is taking advantage of the serious situation on the Korean Peninsula created by outsiders in a desperate bid to stifle the cause of national independence and reunification and bring back the era of inter-Korean confrontation.
 The confrontation fanatics of the GNP, as instructed by outside forces, are vociferating that the war deterrent of the DPRK defending the nation is a threat to the south. They have gone the lengths of blustering that even a war should not be ruled out, not content with crying out for a complete stop to the inter-Korean cooperation and exchange and sanctions against the north in all fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 People will never remain a passive onlooker to such acts of treachery of the GNP as cooperating with outside forces instead of standing by them to frustrate the moves of outside forces for aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation should deal hard blows at these criminal moves of the GNP.
 All Koreans should firmly unite and intensify the anti-GNP actions in order to shatter the moves of the outside forces for aggression against reunification and bring durable peace to the country and achieve national independence and reunification.

Quality Painting Materials Produced
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 30 (KCNA) -- The Korea Jonghyang Foreign Technical Exchange Company in the DPRK produces quality painting materials to meet the ever-increasing demand for them.
 With the very strong adhesive power the materials are strong in resistance to humidity and heat. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular the newly developed Jonghyang-Jinju Sound Absorption Painting Material has been widely used in construction field. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It neither is cracked nor produces pollution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The five-year-long test in the open-air proves that its adhesive power and color remain unchanged. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The company is also manufacturing rust-proofing paint material, distemper paint and other painting materials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-mentioned painting materials have been applied to newly-built or renovated buildings such as Pyongyang Kim Won Gyun Conservatory, Moranbong Theatre, East Pyongyang Grand Theatre and Okryu Restaurant.

Developing DPRK Women's Football
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 30 (KCNA) -- The history of women's football in the DPRK is not long.
 Since a measure was taken in Juche 74(1985) to organize women's football teams, teenage girls began to play football with a dream of displaying the honor of the country.
 It was the South Phyongan Provincial Sports Group (at that time) that organized the women's football team, the first of its kind in the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There was the first training football match of female footballers of the first generation at Kim Il Sung Stadium on May 19, 1986. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recollecting those days, female footballer Kye Yong Sun, 35, told KCNA that the football teams, which came into being amid interests of the country, made match tours to accumulate experience and intensified training to compete with the world strong teams. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK women's football team displayed its ability to the full at the 7th Asian Women's Football Championship in 1988. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the 13th Asian Women's Football Championship (2001), the DPRK team defeated all the opponents by manifesting the firm faith in sure victory, stubborn fighting sprit and a high degree of sports technique, thus wining the championship in the new century. 
 This year the DPRK women's football team won all the six matches at the 3rd FIFA U-20 Women's World Championship to become the strongest in the world.
 Promising is the DPRK women's football team with a large number of reserves.

More than 170 Cases of U.S. Aerial Espionage against DPRK in November
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 30 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialist aggressor forces committed more than 170 cases of aerial espionage against the DPRK by mobilizing strategic and tactical reconnaissance planes with diverse missions in November, according to military sources.
 On Nov. 30 south Korea-based U-2 was busy watching and spying on all areas deep inside the territory of the DPRK for 8 hours. Aerial espionage committed by this type plane in the month numbered more than 20. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On Nov. 7, 16 and 29 overseas-based E-3 committed espionage against the DPRK, while commanding combat flying corps of the U.S. imperialist aggressor forces engaged in anti-DPRK aerial war exercises. On Nov. 22 and 24 EP-3 took off a base in Japan and flew in the air above Taebu Islet and the areas of Hoengsong and Yangphyong at night to photograph and spy on areas of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, two or three RC-7B and RC-12 were busy spying on the frontline areas of the DPRK almost everyday.
